Introduction

SNUPER (Korean: 스누퍼; Japanese: スヌーパー) is a six-member boy group under WIDMAY Entertainment. They officially debuted on November 16, 2015 with their first mini album Shall We. It is the agency's first idol group. They disbanded on May 3, 2023 following the expiration of the members' contracts.

Their name stands for 'higher than super'.
